        "The incredible historic homes used to recreate the royal palaces in The Crown\nHowever, his vision was thwarted by then-UK Prime Minister Winston Churchill. At the time, the documentary explains, the government decided on these royal matters.\n\"Churchill wanted the new Queen in the palace of her ancestors, who had chosen it as an official residence since the time of Queen Victoria,\" Angela adds. A timeline of Queen Elizabeth and Prince Philip's relationship milestones. (9Honey)\nThe Queen and Philip effectively swapped places with the Queen Mother and Princess Margaret, who moved out of Buckingham Palace to Clarence House.\nWhile Buckingham Palace is the Queen's main residence, and was for Prince Philip until he retired from public life in 2017, the couple also frequent their other properties.\nEvery year, the couple spends Easter in Windsor Castle, then heads north during the summer months to relax at Balmoral Castle, their sprawling Scottish estate. The Queen and Prince Philip have spent most of 2020 based at Windsor Castle. (Instagram @theroyalfamily)\nThen, come Christmas time, it's north again to Sandringham House in Norfolk, where they're usually joined by other royal family members for the holiday.\nIn 2020, Windsor Castle became the Queen and Prince Philip's main base, the couple isolating together during the coronavirus pandemic.\nAfter spending summer at Balmoral, the Duke travelled back to Sandringham, where he'd been based since his retirement, while the Queen returned to Windsor Castle. These are the most expensive royal estates, palaces and castles",
