        'Clarke Gayford and Jacinda Ardern have been together since 2013. (Instagram)\nThe pair began dating in 2013, and four years later their relationship became a lot more high-profile.\nIn August 2017, Ardern became the leader of New Zealand\'s Labour Party, and seven weeks later she was elected to the office of Prime Minister.\nRELATED: Clarke Gayford plays family hairdresser during lockdown\nGayford recalled he was diving in Queensland when his partner became Labour leader, sparking "a swift and sudden turn" in their life together.\n"As I was about to go down underwater I turned my phone off, like \'I don\'t want to know about this\'," he told Nova\'s Fitzy and Wippa. "The guy on the boat said, \'Your missus has had a promotion\'." (Getty)\n"When I came back up the guy on the boat said, \'Yeah, mate, you might want to call back home. Your missus has had a promotion\'."\nPolitics and major world events aside, the last three years have produced some major milestones for Ardern and Gayford.\nIn June 2018, the couple welcomed their first child, daughter Neve Te Aroha Ardern Gayford , making Ardern the second world leader to give birth while in office.\nThe following year, they became engaged during the Easter break, with Clarke proposing on top of the Mokotahi Hill in Mahia. Gayford admits the way he met Ardern was "slightly embarrassing". (AP)\nThe broadcaster and fishing enthusiast admits his days look rather different to his fiancee\'s.\nJust last Saturday, she was tied up with a conference requiring calls through the night.\n"She was doing interviews from 12 midnight through to three in the morning. I got up 2.5 hours later and snuck off working, out spearfishing," he laughed. All the times Jacinda Ardern has made the world love her',
