      language: "english",
      text:
        "How to see the Christmas lights safely this year: a state by state guide Tesco – No Naughty List\nUK supermarket chain Tesco addressed the elephant in the room — the global pandemic — but in a cheeky way.\nRather than making it about the sadness of the year gone by, Tesco is encouraging everyone to take on the holidays guilt-free by telling everyone there is \"no naughty list this year\". Marks & Spencer – This is M&S Christmas Food\nThis ad is all about indulgence over the holidays with the finer and more decadent things this supermarket has to offer.\nThe ad is voiced by The Crown star Olivia Colman, so it's perhaps not entirely by accident that they talk about the brand's gin first up — given it's said to be Queen Elizabeth's favourite tipple. Sainsbury's - The Gravy Song\nThis supermarket chain's big Christmas commercial feels a little like it's been inspired by TikTok meets the Kardashians.\nLots of family moments caught on camera to re-iterate how special the holidays can be surrounded by loved ones, while a father and daughter are overheard talking on the phone and hoping they can meet this year ('cause... COVID). Lidl - Big on a Christmas you can believe in\nThis UK supermarket chain pokes fun not only at the pandemic but at Christmas ads in general — their competitor Aldi's ad in particular when talking carrots. McDonald's UK - Inner Child\nMcDonald's UK has gotten nostalgic this year.\nThe fast food giant's animated ad shows a mother struggling to connect with her teenage son who thinks he's too cool for Christmas. Disney – From Our Family to Yours\nThis is another animated one (what else would you expect from Disney?), and it hits you with all the feels.\nGet the tissues ready before watching this one. Coca-Cola Christmas Commercial 2020\nCoca-Cola, rumoured to have invented Santa's red outfit in a Christmas commercial back in the 1930s, is back with a big budget blockbuster this year.\nIt shows the lengths a father will go to after forgetting to post his daughter's letter to the North Pole. Pepsi Max – Refresh Your Christmas\nPepsi isn't competing with Coke on budget or scale, but instead offering a slogan that challenges its soft drink rival.\nThe ad encourages people to try something different over the holidays, saying \"Traditional is cliche\". Amazon - The Show Must Go On\nAmazon has opted for a feel-good commercial but one firmly centred around the pandemic (which, of course, got lots of people shopping for more online this year).\nAfter a young girl's ballet is cancelled, the whole community rallies together for their sentiment that \"the show must go on\". Advent calendars to make your run to Christmas more festive",
