      text:
        "Ben Fordham isn't the sort of bloke to wear a cape\"> Ben Fordham isn't the sort of bloke to wear a cape , as stylish as he is, but we're thinking he ought to start after coming to the rescue of a stressed-out bride this morning who was facing the prospect of getting married without her beloved brother in attendance, and two bridesmaids down.\n\"Oh my God it's been the most ridiculous 24 hours or even longer,\" Cassie Brien, 30, tells 9Honey. \"I'm exhausted just from this morning, but I'm over the moon after what's happened today.\"\nHer brother Patrick, 28, and his partner Madeline are New South Wales residents but became stranded in Victoria during the coronavirus pandemic . With lockdown lifted the couple had been applying for permission to enter the state in time for Sunday's nuptials but had been unsuccessful. Patrick and Madeline have been stuck in Victoria due to the pandemic. (Supplied)\nAdded to that, two of Cassie's bridesmaids weren't able to make it either - one who lives in Canada and one who lives in South Australia and was about to board a flight to Sydney with her family when the six-day lockdown was announced there.\nCassie and Patrick were devastated he wouldn't make it to the wedding but had accepted it was the case.\n\"We got so close,\" she says. \"We had tried everything but just had to come to terms with it.\"\nFor a daily dose of 9Honey, sign up here to receive our top stories straight to your inbox Patrick was unable to gain approval to enter NSW in time for his sister's wedding. (Supplied)\nThat's when Cassie's best friend Brittany Jarochowicz, 32, reached out to 2GB Live host Ben Fordham for help.\nRELATED: Bridesmaid threatens bride with legal action over cancelled wedding\nCassie got through to Fordham this morning and explained the situation to a sympathetic Fordham. The call ended with Brittany thinking that was that. There was nothing anyone could do to help her. We are in the middle of a pandemic after all. Brittany (left) reached out to Ben Fordham to help with Cassie's wedding dilemma. (Supplied)\nCassie and Brittany were in the middle of a pilates class just hour later when Brittany's phone rang. It was New South Wales Health who has been contacted by Fordham for help to bring Cassie's brother Patrick to Sydney in time for the wedding.\nBrittany says she was shocked to receive the call. Brittany and Cassie have been best friends since childhood. (Supplied)\n\"NSW Health rang me and told us it had been organised and Cass is beyond ecstatic,\" she says. \"Then Ben Fordham rang her brother and now Patrick has a written letter of approval for both of them.\"\nBrittany is so grateful to Fordham for his help.\n\"I always listen to 2GB and my friends laugh at me about it but I learn so much from talk back and he's so easy to listen to. I'm just super-grateful to Ben and NSW Health, they are absolute legends.\"\nListen to Ben Fordham talk to Brittany this morning on Ben Fordham Live on 2GB. Article continue.\nCassie is thrilled with the outcome and has even managed to find replacement bridesmaids for the event.\n\"Luckily one of my amazing beautiful friends Marla is jumping in for my friend in Canada and my sister-in-law is jumping in for my friend in South Australia,\" she says.\nWhile Marla's bridesmaid's dress had already been sorted another one was needed to replace the one left stranded in South Australia after the borders and post offices closed. Cassie and Jay will be married on Sunday with Patrick and his partner in attendance. (Matt Ashton Photograhy)\n\"I got the dresses from Sheike last summer and I asked if they might have another one in one of their stores and we found it in a mid-city store for $50,\" she says.\nCassie and her family is thrilled Patrick is coming to the wedding. She says lockdown has been hard for him and his partner.\n\"It's been a crazy time for them for their mental health,\" she says.\nWhen it was announced that the borders between Victoria and NSW would open on November 23, the family made peace with the fact Patrick would arrive a day after the wedding, although they had decided to drive to the border earlier on the off chance they may be let in earlier and make it to at least part of the wedding. Both Britanny and Cassie have called Ben Fordham a 'legend'. (Supplied)\n\"Then when they found out this morning they could come they were beside themselves.,\" Cassie says. \"It's real, it's happening.\n\"Their lease is nearly up and they didn't know if they were going to be homeless. They had tried everything and had contacted everyone they knew for help.\"\nThe wedding will take place on Sunday at Bowral and thanks to Fordham it is going to be an incredible event.\n\"He's a dead set legend,\" Cassie says of Fordham. \"He's so genuine. He even rang Britt a couple of times after it was all sorted. He's a beautiful human and the health minister is amazing that they can do this for us after such a crazy year.\"\nCassie and Jay met at a backyard party when they were 15 and reconnected three years ago.\n\"We were supposed to be in Mexico and Las Vegas and LA for our honeymoon but I have two stepkids so we'll probably just go down to Mollymook in an Airbnb and when we drop the kids back we'll go to Sydney and eat in our favourite restaurant.\"\nShare your story by emailing Jo Abi at jabi@nine.com.au. The most extravagant royal weddings of modern times",
