      text:
        'By Karishma Sarkari | 41 minutes ago\nJacinda Ardern has shared a sweet post, reflecting on her "first overseas trip" as a 12-year-old, which happened to be to Australia.\nThe now-Prime Minister of New Zealand shared a photo on Instagram of a souvenir she still has that was bought at Movie World during the family vacation to Queensland.\n"Finishing up some papers with a cup of tea tonight when I couldn\'t help but dwell for a minute over the mug that Clarke made it in," the now 40-year-old told fans. Jacinda Ardern has shared a sweet post, reflecting on her "first overseas trip" as a 12-year-old, which happened to be to Australia (Instagram/JacindaArdern)\n"When I was about 12, my family went to Australia for our first overseas trip together. It was my first time on a plane, and I remember being so excited. I spent months making Dad explain to me every element of a plane ride, including the airport."\nThe PM revealed her parents had "saved hard" to pay for the trip to the Sunshine State, where they stayed with family in Brisbane.\nThe family took Ms Ardern\'s grandad along on the trip, which was shortly after her nana passed away.\n"He very rarely left Te Aroha, he never, ever wore shorts even in the summer, so I remember being really surprised but really happy he came," Ms Ardern said.',
