        "Child & Adolescent Psychologist About Us: Kids At Max focusses on support for children and adolescents between 2-18 years of age. We are proud to be a highly regarded family clinic. We offer a range of services including psychology, speech pathology, occupational therapy, social skills groups, school readiness programs and school consultation services. Our vision is to provide kids and families with a professional service that supports ongoing development and encourages them to live a healthy and happy lifestyle. We believe in working from a strengths based perspective, and we acknowledge and encourage a child's unique abilities. We work with the child and their family to develop skills to support them to succeed socially, emotionally and behaviourally. The Role: We have a position for a Psychologist to join us on a part time or full time basis. Why Join Us: A friendly, engaging and collaborative team who love what they do. A friendly, engaging and collaborative team who love what they do. We encourage innovation and work within best practice modes of therapy and assessment for each discipline. An extensive shared resource library with therapy tools and assessments for psychology, speech pathology, occupational therapy and education support. Ongoing support to meet your CPD requirements including professional development planning and paid PD leave. Ongoing support is tailored to suit your skill level, experience and professional requirements to ensure you are able to provide best practice support. Administration and diary management support. A professional and relaxed team environment. Regular scheduled individual / group supervision and support with the team. Formal training in assessment tools such as ADOS-2\nStrong work ethic and desire to work as part of a team and independently. Reliable and committed to providing a high quality of service to clients. Ability to positively engage with children, adolescents and families. Full registration as a Psychologist with AHPRA. Eligibility for registration as a Medicare provider. Working With Children Check. Kids At Max is a registered provider for children and adolescents with funding from DHHS, Helping Children With Autism, NDIS, Medicare, Better Start Initiative and TAC. How to Apply: If this sounds like an opportunity you would be interested in, please email your CV and cover letter to The Directors of Kids At Max.",
