      text:
        "Supporting Aussie businesses is even more important this year.\nAh, the Christmas season is almost upon us, and if you, like us, are scrambling on what to buy your nearest and dearest then look no further. We've pulled in the help of model and Myer Ambassador Elyse Knowles who shared with us her ultimate gift guide for inspiration.\nBut there's a twist. Elyse is passionate about turning this Christmas into an opportunity to help Australia born-and-bred businesses.\nShe says, \"along with my Myer family, we'd love to remind all Australians that the best way to give this Christmas is to support Australian businesses and buy local. Giving the gift of homemade and home-grown this year will not only spread the Christmas cheer, it will help rebuild families and restore lost hope. Be kind, give with your heart and stay safe.\"\nWe couldn't agree more. So what are the Melburnian model's top picks? Well, here they are: Palm Beach Collection\nIt's universally understood that candles are always – and we mean, always - a welcomed gift, and they don't get much better than the Palm Beach Collection. These individually hand-poured candles are luxurious yet affordable. There's also reed diffusers and bath products that ensure these are a great gift choice for mums, sisters or besties.\nElyse says, \"Each of the fragrances are inspired by Australia's coastal landscape which is a perfect present from me being based in Byron!\" Eco Tan\n\"This is one of my favourites,\" says Elyse. \"It's a certified organic self-tan skincare and body range that gives you the best sun-kissed glow. They have many gift sets including The Facial Gift Box, Hydration Skin System set or even just their infamous Face Tan Water which are the perfect gifts.\"\nA great one for the bronze goddesses in your life. Hunter Lab\n\"A great Aussie brand for those males you don't know what to buy for,\" explains Elyse of Hunter Lab, a Melbourne-made skincare brand that's created only from natural ingredients.\nBest of all, they now offer some incredible gifts including the Hunter Essentials Gift Set, Hand & Body kits and more. That's the men in your life sorted. Random Harvest\nEvery family as The Host, the one who loves opening-up their home for entertaining. And this is the ultimate gift for them. Random Harvest hampers are packed with goodies that level up a dinner party, such as mustards, chutneys, dessert, savoury sauces, tapenades, dressings, jams and even confectionery.\nElyse adds, \"This year our Christmas celebrations need to go beyond the tinsel and the carols. This year our Christmas celebrations need to go right into the homes and hearts of those who have had a really rough trot and who sincerely deserve to enjoy a time of joy, rest and comfort.\"\nAfter all the missed events this year, there's only one place to make up for it. Myer has endless gift ideas all in one place to make your celebrations bigger than Christmas. Style",
