        'Wife reveals the source of holes in her bed sheets and people are horrified\nThe video, that\'s since been viewed over 1.2 million times, quickly reveals the simple reason why the light won\'t go off.\nAs her husband complies with her wishes and flicks the series of light switches in the couple\'s downstairs room, he finally informs her of the reason.\n"Babe it\'s a skylight," he explains.\nAs the camera pans across the room, the man notes she\'s been trying to turn off the sun. The video, that\'s since been viewed over 1.2 million times, quickly reveals the simple reason why the light won\'t go off. (TikTok)\n"It\'s the sunlight," he says, laughing.\n"So there\'s a hole cut out on the roof for that?" she responds.\nThe man, who captioned the video "my wife may be slightly special", asks his wife "Feel stupid?" to which she replies, "Yeah I do," before walking off.\nDrawing over 2700 comments, users were widely confused as to why the wife never realised the \'light\' in question turned off… at sunset.\n"Has she never lived in your house past 7 pm?" asked one user.\n"Tell her it\'s controlled by the sky," joked another.\nWhile many users also jumped to the wife\'s defence, claiming skylight\'s are "confusing."\n"Not gonna lie, the house I\'m in now has one of these and it took me a couple days to figure it out," confessed one user.\n"It was bright enough, I thought it was a light," said another.\nCall it a \'light bulb\' moment.',
